Machosexual: (MAH-choh-SEK-shoo-ul), noun. A man who eschews modern aesthetics in favor of other, more traditional manly pursuits. A machosexual exhibits personality traits common to traditional male roles, and fulfills classic male functions. For example, machosexuals will not wax their body hair, because having chest and back hair is a natural male trait. Machosexuals are dominant, and heroic. Typical machosexual occupations include Police Officer, Soldier, Landscape Artist, Musician, Auto Mechanic, and Firefighter. A machosexual can still exhibit sensitive qualities, especially in his concern for his mate or family. Machosexuals do not necessarily give up good grooming habits, in fact, they generally take very good care of their bodies. They simply revert to traditional haircare, traditional facial shaving patterns, and traditional styles of dress.

